      "description": "*Since I am using Lunox as a Roamer, I use Conceal as my Roamer Blessing and now winning after switching to Roamer Lunox.\n\n*Lunox With Wilderness Blessing can rotate to teammates and enemies.\n\n*Since Lunox is a Roamer, other mages can fill up the Mage slot for more CC, sustain or some weird Mid Lane Pick liek Gusion r Esmeralda.\n\n*Explanation for the Lack of Common Items - All of these are alternative items instead of the primary items seen in this build. Saving Items such as Immortality and Winter Crown because they are very situational and need a lot of planning before and post usage, so I recommend these 2 to be in the Spare section of your builds, mine are different items, still testing what needs to be there.\n\n1. Glowing Wand - I only use this item if there are many tanks or bulky fighters. Or the annoying healers or Sustain Heroes\n2. Arcane Boots - I need more CD Reduction and i do not need this for now, especially as a Roamer since I need to get more skills off.\n3. Winter Truncheon - I already have enough damage.\n\nWhy the weird items?\nFleeting Time - In Epic (will be in Epic again after not playing for a very, very long time since I always played Honor of Kings for more than a year straight), teammates can't get things done, so instead of waiting and tilting, for every kill or assist, i get 30% of my Ultimate CD reduced, so if I assisted in 2 or 3 i can have my Chaos Ultimate again, same applies with light. Season 39 ends in less than 10 days so Epic 2 or 3.\n\nIce Queen Wand - Since I am new to Lunox and trying her out to expand my Roamer hero pool (becoming one of my mains as Roamer), I'm not as skilled in microgame that uses her Skill 3 and her 2nd Skill enhanced by Ultimate, enemies can escape, so to lessen it and get more slow, I use this item.\n\nWhy Flicker?\nI use Flicker to escape post-Order Ultimate if I don't have enough distance. Except vs Yin (especially this 1v1 forcer) or other lockdown heroes, you will be dead if you used Flicker.\n\nCan I use Demon Shoes? Yes, especially for mana reasons and you want Lethal Ignition instead of Impure Rage, go ahead, fully recommended.",
